<p>I have a hyperlink in a gridview cell which works fine, however in order to improve the experience of my users I would like the whole cell to be clickable rather than just the text as in most cases the text is a single digit.</p>  <p>e.g.</p>  <pre><code>&lt;asp:TemplateField HeaderText="Qty"&gt;     &lt;ItemTemplate&gt;         &lt;asp:HyperLink ID="Lnk" runat="server"            NavigateUrl='&lt;%# "View.aspx?ID=" + Eval("ID") %&gt;'            Text='&lt;%# Eval("Qty") %&gt;' /&gt;     &lt;/ItemTemplate&gt; &lt;/asp:TemplateField&gt; </code></pre>  <p>How can I make the entire table cell clickable?</p>